column493:
Children up to age 18 are eligible for care at Shriners Hospitals for Children. Admission is restricted to children. However, some patients over the age of 18 were reviewed, evaluated and admitted for the purposes of care continuity. The hospital performs very complex surgeries that often require sequential surgeries and follow-up over a period of time. A surgeon follows and monitors this care, which sometimes may extend past the age of 18.

Each admission of a patient over 18 is evaluated and reviewed on a case-by-case basis.
